Durban - The "knocker gang", a group of men who rob unsuspecting residents as they leave banks after withdrawing large sums of money, has struck again. This time, they robbed a man at the Phoenix Plaza on Monday morning. It is alleged that four men, armed with rifles robbed a business man as he got left a bank and walked towards his vehicle. According to sources at the scene, shots were fired as the gang fled the scene but no injuries were reported.  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. At the weekend, a cellphone shop at City View was robbed. Marshall Security spokesperson, Kyle van Reenen, said a number of armed suspects stormed the shop at about 8am on Sunday. "The staff were tied up. Cellphones were taken. No one was injured," he said. He said in a separate incident at the Windermere Shopping Centre, a woman was robbed of her gold chain. Van Reenen said the assailant had a firearm and fired two shots into the air. No injuries were reported. The Mercury